<DOCNO> XIE19980901.0002 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Major Banks Raise Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 31 (Xinhua) -- All major South African
commercial banks have raised their prime lending rate and
mortgage rate after First National Bank (FNB) announced its rate
hikes on Monday.
</P>
<P>
FNB's prime rate would go up by 1.5 percentage points to 25.5
percent per annum, immediately effective, and the base mortgage
rate by two percentage points to 24 percent per annum, effective
for new applicants and existing borrowers from September 2.
</P>
<P>
The Standard Bank, Allied Bank of South Africa and NBS Boland
increased their rates Friday, followed by Nedcor, another leading
bank in South Africa on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The new round of interest rate hikes came after a hectic week
in which shock waves from political and economic turmoil in
Russia hit South Africa and other emerging markets across the
world.
</P>
<P>
The Johannesburg Stock Exchange crashed with the value of its
shares losing 17 percent in the week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
