<HEADLINE> Negasso Calls for Renovation of Ethio-Kenyan Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian President Negasso
Gidada Monday called for the renovation of Moyale-Isiolo road in
a bid to strengthen the Ethio-Kenyan relations especially in the
sphere of trade.
</P>
<P>
President Negasso made the remarks here when he was meeting
the outgoing Kenyan Ambassador to Ethiopia, Geoffrey K. Muriithi,
the Ethiopian News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
President Negasso said that renovating the road will
facilitate the smooth conduct of trade between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The report said that Ambassador Muriithi on his part expressed
his country's willingness to renovate the Moyale-Isiolo road.
</P>
<P>
The over-500-kilometer-long Moyale-Isiolo road which links
Ethiopia's southern border town of Moyale with Kenya's town of
Isiolo, is a south-north main road linking the two neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
The renovation of the Moyale-Isiolo road will strengthen the
road transport between the two countries, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian president also expressed sympathy over the death
of innocent people in Kenya by the terrorist bomb and indicated
the need for neighboring countries to join hands in fighting
against such acts of terrorism, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
