<HEADLINE> Floods Kill 998 in North India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 31 (Xinhua) -- At least 78 more people were
killed Monday by floods in Utter Pradesh, north India, raising the
toll to 998 as the overall flood situation remained grim in the
state, according to the Press Trust of India (PTI).
</P>
<P>
With some rivers flowing above the danger mark, the local
government Monday declared three districts in the state as
flood-hit.
</P>
<P>
The Army was assisting the civil administration in evacuating
affected people in the worst-hit areas and helicopters dropped
food packets in Gorakhpur district of the state, said PTI.
</P>
<P>
The floods, which began four weeks ago, have affected large
areas in Utter Pradesh, Bihar, Haryana and Assam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
