<HEADLINE> UK Considering to Call G7 Meeting on Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Labor government is
considering to call a meeting of the Group of Seven (G7)
industrial nations to discuss the worsening Russian financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
A Downing Street spokesman was quoted by Reuters as saying here
Monday, "The possibility of a meeting in some form of G7 leaders
is being actively considered."
</P>
<P>
"There'll be a decision in the next few days, once we know the
shape of the new government in Russia... we need to know who we're
dealing with," he said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past weekend, British Prime Minister Tony Blair, whose
country is the current G7 president, held a series of telephone
discussions with other G7 leaders to exchange views on the Russian
situation.
</P>
<P>
All the G7 leaders have pledged that it was in their interests
to help the Russian government to get through the current
financial difficulties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
