<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Drops Below 8,000 for 1st Time in Seven Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Dow industrials fell below
8,000 Monday morning for the first time in seven months, a drop
that wiped out all of this year's gains.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average was down 165.03 at 7,886.65 at
late morning on trading volume that was active but below last
week's frenzied pace.
</P>
<P>
With Monday morning's losses, the Dow gave up the last of this
year's gains. It ended 1997 at 7,908.25. The last time the Dow
closed below 8,000 was on Jan. 30.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Wall Street stock market was heavily hit by an
international financial turmoil caused by the Russian economic
crisis.
</P>
<P>
Some press reports said Monday that after world stock markets
were hit with hurricane force last week by Russia's problems,
there may be more storm ahead. 
</P>
