peace, improved security and the stability of local currency and
prices in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that the event will bring a profit of some
200,000 U.S. Dollars since 55,000 people will visit the
400,000-U.S.-Dollar exhibition near the Indian Ocean port of
Maputo.
</P>
<P>
Among the 300 dignitaries who attended the opening ceremony
were Mozambican Minister of Industry, Trade and Tourism Oldemiro
Baloi, General Secretary of the ruling Mozambique Liberation
Front Manuel Tome, President of the biggest opposition party
Mozambican National Resistance Afonso Dhlakama and some foreign
diplomats. 
