<HEADLINE> Refugees Fleeing into Tanzania Exceed 1,800 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The number of refugees
flowing into Tanzania from the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC)
has surpassed 1,800, a United Nations refugee agency official
said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR)
Kigoma sub-office head, J.F.Durieux said that as time goes on,
the number of refugees fleeing civil strife in the DRC keeps
rising, reaching 1,823 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The refugees crossed Lake Tanganyika by boat into Kigoma in
west Tanzania after the Tutsi-led rebels took up arms in Goma of
the eastern DRC.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, UNHCR officials said that the influx of refugees is
manageable, as they are capable of handling even 1,000 new
arrivals a day.
</P>
<P>
All the refugees UNHCR has received are civilians and no
rebellion soldiers are among them, said Durieux.
</P>
<P>
The DRC refugees are being sheltered at Nyarugusu camp in the
Kasulu district while 1,148 Burundian refugees received this
month are sheltered at Nduta camp, Kibondo district, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
