<HEADLINE> Turkey Concerned About Situation in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Turkey Monday expressed deep
concern over the continuing clashes in Afghanistan, describing
them as "fratricide."
</P>
<P>
"Turkey regrets the continuation of the armed conflict in
Afghanistan and believes in the establishment of peace and
stability in the country," a statement issued by the Foreign
Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The problems in Afghanistan should be solved through peaceful
means instead of resorting to force, it said, adding that forming
a broad-based government is the best way to achieve peace and
stability in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Fierce fightings have been continuing between the opposition
Northern Alliance and the Taliban forces, which have won control
over most areas of the country.
</P>
<P>
Turkey condemned the human rights violations committed by the
Taliban forces in northern Afghanistan, saying that it would
continue to watch closely the developments there.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the statement rejected claims in the Pakistani press
that Turkey is trying to exert influence on Afghanistan for
consideration of energy.
</P>
<P>
"It is not realistic to postulate a similarity between
Turkey's policy on Afghanistan and oil and gas pipelines," it said.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has reportedly urged Pakistan, Taliban's strong
supporter, to prevent the militia from harming civilians and
innocent people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
