<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, August 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Five Israeli soldiers were wounded early Monday in an
attack by the Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, in south
Lebanon, Lebanon's Voice of the People radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The five were wounded in the explosion of a remote-controlled
bomb planted at the Dabshi village in the central sector of the
Israeli occupied zone in south Lebanon when an Israeli patrol was
passing by.
</P>
<P>
But Israeli radio said four Israeli soldiers were wounded by a
helicopter accident. (BC-South Lebanon-Israelis Wounded)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf Denktash Monday proposed
a confederation composed of the Greek and Turkish communities in
Cyprus to end the 24-year-old division of the island.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Turkish Cypriot regime reaching here
termed the proposal as "a final effort" to achieve a mutually
acceptable lasting solution in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Denktash made the proposal for the confederation of "two
peoples and two states" at a press conference in Nicosia with the
presense of visiting Turkish Foreign Minister Ismail Cem.
</P>
<P>
The condition Denktash set to the negotiations for the
confederation is the acknowledgement of the Turkish Cypriot side
as a "sovereign and equal" state as the Greek Cypriot side.
(BC-Turkey-Cyprus-Proposal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan left here
for Khartoum on a two-day visit to Sudan for consultations with
Sudan on combating anti-Iraq and anti-Sudan actions of the
U.S. and Israel, Iraqi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted Ramadan as saying that his visit to
Sudan came within the context of consultation and dialog between
the two countries on confronting the schemes and atrocities
carried out by the Americans and the Zionists.
</P>
<P>
He will hold talks with Sudanese President Omar Hassan Ahmed
al-Bashir, said the report. (BC-Iraq-Vice President-Sudan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat Monday accused Israel
of balking at a U.S. proposal calling for Israeli withdrawal from
another 13.1 percent of the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu is "still placing
hurdles in the way of the American proposal," Arafat told a press
conference jointly held with Jordanian Crown Prince Hassan after
their meeting here.
</P>
<P>
"We stick to the American proposal," Arafat said, adding that
the Palestinians remain committed to the peace process as "a
strategic option." (BC-Jordan-Arafat-Israel)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
\  NICOSIA -- Cyprus' President Glafcos Clerides Monday flatly
rejected a proposal put forward by Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash for establishing a Cyprus Confederation, the Cyprus News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
In a written statement issued from South Africa, where he is
attending the Non-Aligned Movement summit, Clerides said the
intention behind Denktash's proposal was to render an independent
sovereign state into two protectorates, governed by unacceptable
restrictions.
</P>
<P>
He denounced Denktash's proposal as "new Turkish provocative
action" and urged the international community to respond directly
to it. (BC-Cyprus-Denktash-Proposal) 
</P>
