Ritter was to divert attention from the inspectors' refusal to
acknowledge Iraq's achievements in eliminating its weapons.
</P>
<P>
Iraq also accused UNSCOM of deliberately prolonging its work
of identifying and destroying Iraq's weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
 Iraq demands a serious investigation of all these facts,
said the letter, adding UNSCOM should be made "an honest
international body, not an intelligence unit for a member
country."  
