<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Exert Efforts for Peaceful Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi said Monday that Ethiopia will exert its efforts
toward the peaceful settlement of the crisis in the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian prime minister made the remarks when he returned
home from a three-day visit to four eastern and southern African
countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Ethiopian News Agency, Meles said
that the crisis in the DRC posed a threat not only to the peace
in that country but also to the continent as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Meles said Ethiopia, together with the Organization of African
Unity (OAU), will do everything in its capacity to avert the
situation in that central African country.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the Ethiopian prime minister met with
presidents of Uganda, Zimbabwe, South Africa, Democratic Congo
and Rwanda and discussed at length with the heads of state about
the situation in the DRC and the ways of peacefully resolving the
crisis in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meles said that the consultations held with all the leaders
proved the complexity and gravity of the situation in the DRC,
which calls for joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
The leaders with whom the Ethiopian prime minister held
discussions have reached a consensus that the OAU should make a
speedy move through its central organ, the Mechanism for Conflict
Prevention, Management and Resolution, so as to find a peaceful
solution to the crisis in Democratic Congo, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
