<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Team Leaves for Commonwealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A 33-member Bangladeshi team is
scheduled to leave here Wednesday for Malaysia to take part in
the 16th Commonwealth games which will begin on September 11 in
Kuala Lumpur, the official BSS news agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi team will take part in only two sports of
cricket and shooting, instead of the original five. Bangladesh
first planned to send an 84-member team to take part in the
games, but since the country has been seriously hit by
devastating flood, the scale of the team reduced to only 33
members to save funds under the directive of Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina.
</P>
<P>
The 11-member shooting team includes four women shooters.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh would have a chance to get a medal in shooting,
officials of the Bangladesh Shooting Federation (BSF) hoped,
since BSF had invited well-known German shooting coach who came
here in mid-August to train Bangladeshi shooters.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh earned its first ever gold medal in shooting in the
14th Commonwealth Games held in Auckland, New Zealand, in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladeshi cricket team is comprised of 14 cricketers,
and they will play their first matches against Babados, South
Africa and North Ireland. 
</P>
