<HEADLINE> Tibet Cancels 33rd Anniversary Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Some 25 percent of the total
population in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region are
engaged in flood control efforts and today's 33 anniversary of the
region's founding passed without fanfare or celebrations.
</P>
<P>
However, a flag-raising ceremony was held this morning in the
Potala Palace Square in Lhasa to commemorate the founding of the
autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
While various parts of the region are in the grips of heavy
flood, the regional government has refrained from requesting
assistance from the central government due to the severity of
devastating floods in the Yangtze River Valley and northeast China.
</P>
<P>
"The central government has never hesitated to support the
autonomous region during difficult periods over the past 33
years," said a senior regional official, adding that "we will
manage to defeat this year's rampant floods on our own."
</P>
<P>
The regional government has decided to cancel a number of
unnecessary meetings and various overseas trips by government
officials. In addition, government departments will be prohibited
from purchasing new automobiles during the second half of this
year. 
</P>
