<HEADLINE> Beijing Sees Rise in Disastrous Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Beijing reported a hefty 13.2
percent rise in fires during the first eight months of the year
and the city's fire departments cautioned the public against
related dangers.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,647 fires were reported in the Chinese capital during
the January-June period, with related events killing 19 and
injuring 49 people. Total economic losses were estimated at around
30 million yuan (3.75 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The fires were mostly caused by electric appliances,
carelessness and smoking, according to officials with the Beijing
Fire Prevention Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Some 69,574 fires, or 386 fires daily, were reported
nationwide during the first half of the year, Fires killed 1,095
people nationwide. 
</P>
