<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Customs Port Opens in Suzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The new customs port which
opened today in the scenic city of Suzhou in east China's Jiangsu
Province will both reduce the time required for customs
inspections and cut expenses.
</P>
<P>
Lulu Port, located in Weiting Township in the Suzhou Industrial
Park, will handle customs inspections withing 24 hours, or in a
substantially shorter period than the five days required when
shipments passed through Shanghai Customs.
</P>
<P>
Approximately 20 percent of the passing through Shanghai Port
in 1997 were either imported or exported by ventures in
Suzhou. according to Xie Jiabin, director of the Management
Committee of the Suzhou Industrial Park.
</P>
<P>
The industrial park is currently home to 109 foreign-funded
enterprises, with the number continuing to grow on annual
basis. The General Administration of Customs approved the port as
part of an effort to attract increased foreign investment and
promote regional economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
