<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Dispatches Reduced Squads for Commonwealth Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DACCA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will dispatch a
reduced delegation to compete in the 16th Commonwealth Games in
Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, officials here said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 33-member Bangladesh delegation will leave here on
Wednesday, including 25 athletes to compete in two sports of
shooting and cricket.
</P>
<P>
Originally, Bangladesh was schedueled to send an 84-member
delegation to compete in six sports of athletics, cricket, field
hockey, swimming, shooting and weightlifting, but had to cancel
other sports due to floods disaster.
</P>
<P>
However, Bangladesh still pinns its medal hopes in the
sharpshooters by recruiting German coaches for its 11
participants.
</P>
<P>
In 1990, Bangladesh won the gold medal in shooting in the 14th
Commonwealth Games in Auckland, New Zealand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
