<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets New Zealand Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee,
said today that China has scored major victories in food control,
but noted that nation is still confronted with an arduous task.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark while briefing New Zealand Defense Minister
Max Bradford and his delegation on China's massive flood control
effort.
</P>
<P>
He said actions during the ongoing flood control efforts prove
that China's highly disciplined and well organized military forces
have been extremely effective in whole-heartedly serving the
people.
</P>
<P>
Li noted that China values friendly cooperative relations with
New Zealand and is satisfied with the steady development of
bilateral relations since the two nations forged diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
China and New Zealand, both of which are located in the
Asian-Pacific Region, enjoy broad prospects for bilateral
cooperation, said Li.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader noted that exchanges between the two armed
forces are a manifestation of the friendship between people in the
two nations. He expressed hope for the further development of
between the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Bradford expressed his concern about China's flood
situation. He noted that New Zealand and China enjoy a close
cooperative relationship by citing the constant contacts
between the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed hope the visit will further strengthen mutual
understanding and friendship between the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Bradford lauded China's ongoing efforts to ease the Asian
financial crisis.  
</P>
</TEXT>
