<HEADLINE> Macao Sets up Committee to Celebrate 49th Anniversary of PRC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Preparatory Committee for
Macao Compatriots to Celebrate 49th Anniversary of the Founding of
the People's Republic of China (PRC) was established here on
Tuesday, and right after that the first plenum of the committee
was held.
</P>
<P>
The committee is composed of 337 celebrities in Macao, with Ma Man
Kei as executive chairman of the committee's presidium.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the committee members, Ma Man Kei said that over the
past four decades compatriots in Macao have felt pleased when they
see achievements on the motherland, and they belief that a strong
motherland is the fundamental guarantee for Macao's stability and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In the past days, Macao residents have been paying close
attention to the floods in parts of the motherland and offered
donations in time, which "embodies the fine tradition of loving
the motherland among compatriots in Macao and shows the strong
cohesive force of the Chinese nation," Ma said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the wish that the various celebrations in Macao to
mark the 49th anniversary of the founding of new China will further
enhance patriotism among Macao compatriots and unite people of all
walks of life in Macao to create a harmonious environment, so as to
ensure a smooth transition of Macao.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Xinhua News Agency Macao branch, Wang Qiren,
director of the branch, said at the plenum that he expects to see
successful celebration activities. 
</P>
