Carlos Alberto Parreira has been sought by the South African
football association for his service, officials said here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Beside the Brazil, the association also talked to English
managers Ron Atkinson and Howard Wilkinson to gauge their
interest to succeed Frenchman Philippe Troussier, chief executive
officer Danny Jordaan said.
</P>
<P>
Jordaan said Wilkinson, the former Leeds United manager and
now director of coaching for the English Football Association,
had expressed his interest.
</P>
<P>
Parreira coached Brazil to the 1994 World Cup title and but
became the first coach to be fired during the World Cup finals as
Saudi Arabia lost their first two games this summer.
</P>
<P>
After its early exit from the World Cup finals, South Africa
has published advertisements for the coaching position but had a
miserable response with only five candidates expressed their
interests.
</P>
<P>
"We were forced to ask FIFA to help us with a list of suitable
names because of the dismal response," Jordaan said.
</P>
<P>
He said a short list would be drawn up by the end of the week
and a final decision made later this month. 
</P>
