<HEADLINE> Romania to Impose Life Bans for Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Romania will impose life
bans to any doping offender starting from 1999, the Romanian
Olympic authorities said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The Romanian Olympic Committee (COR) will ban any competitor
involved in any sort of doping activity as from January 1, 1999,"
COR vice-president Cristian Gatu said.
</P>
<P>
Gatu said the decision, adopted by the COR's Council on
Monday, would apply to anyone associated with the offence,
including athletes, doctors, coaches and managers.
</P>
<P>
Since 1989, Romanian athletics authorities have imposed bans
of two years to life on 15 world and Olympic medalists. 
