<HEADLINE> Donations Distributed to Flood-Ravaged Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
distributed over 200 million yuan (25 million US dollars) in
donated cash and relief materials valued at 40.92 million yuan in
flood-ravaged areas on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also granted approval for the distribution of a
Red Cross Society of China donation of 145 million yuan and funds
totalling 7.82 million yuan from the China Charity Federation.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials said that all donated funds, with exception
of the donation from the Red Cross Society of China, will be used
for epidemic control and the treatment of diseases. Government
allocated funds will be earmarked for building new homes for flood
victims.
</P>
<P>
The bulk of allocated funds and materials were sent to
provinces and regions suffering the heaviest damage from summer
flooding, including Jiangxi, Hunan, Hubei, Heilongjiang, Jilin and
Anhui provinces, and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region. Smaller
amounts were earmarked for various other areas, including Fujian
Province and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
August statistics released by Ministry of Civil Affairs
Ministry show that donations by the ministry's offices nationwide,
the Red Cross Society of China and the China Charity Federation
totalled 2.88 billion yuan. Some 1.69 billion yuan has already been
distributed to flood-ravaged areas. 
</P>
