<HEADLINE> Hongkong Post Introduces Speedpost Insurance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Hongkong Post launched
Tuesday Speedpost Insurance - a new service designed to offer
customers complete peace of mind when sending packages overseas.
</P>
<P>
The new service, underwritten by Winterthur Swiss Insurance
(Asia) Ltd. and marketed by Zuellig Insurance Brokers (HK) Ltd.,
provides additional coverage to documents, samples and merchandise
against loss or damage whilst being sent from Hong Kong to
overseas countries through Speedpost.
</P>
<P>
Under this optional service, five different plans have been
developed to cater for different customer needs. The premium
starts from 35 HK dollars (4.5 U.S. dollars) to 175 HK dollars
(22.4 U.S. dollars), with coverage ranging from 10,000 HK dollars
(1,282 U.S. dollars) to a maximum of 50,000 HK dollars (6,410 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Announcing the launch of Speedpost Insurance at a ceremony
Tuesday, Postmaster General Robert Footman said the new service is
part of Hongkong Post's ongoing effort to provide more value-added
services to customers.
</P>
<P>
"As a service provider striving to achieve high levels of
customer satisfaction, Hongkong Post always looks for new
initiatives to enhance our services," Footman said.
</P>
<P>
Speedpost has one of the largest delivery networks in the
world, serving 82 countries, including 1,900 cities in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
