<HEADLINE> China Tightens Controls Over Medical Supplies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Health has
just issued instructions for strengthened supervision to ensure
the quality of pharmaceuticals in order to prevent shipments of
fake and low quality medicines to flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Ministry of Health, State Economic and Trade
Commission, Ministry of Civil Affairs, and State Bureau of
Pharmaceutical Supervision and Management recently issued a joint
circular instructing all medical professionals to strictly abide
by the rules for medical care and of the use of medical products.
</P>
<P>
The circular forbids the use of expired or uncertified medical,
and demands safe transportation for related products.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health reported that the central government's
first shipment of medical supplies included 19,910 items valued at
over 30 million yuan. The shipment was distributed in Hubei,
Jiangxi, Hunan and Jilin provinces, with an additional shipment en
route to Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Railways issued a notice instructing railway
stations in eight provinces, including Hunan, to make every effort
to ensure that the medical supplies arrive in flood-stricken areas
as soon as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
