<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Civil Affairs Ministry Calls for Donations to Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
has urged economically developed provinces and municipalities
which have escaped this year's ravaging floods to provide
emergency aid to flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Nonaffected areas are required to provide disaster relief
items, especially badly needed quilts and winter clothing, to
flood-ravaged areas, according to the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The ministry called on Beijing and Tianjin municipalities, and
Hebei, Liaoning and Shandong provinces to collect cotton clothing
and quilts for areas along the Nen and Songhua rivers in
Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region in northeast China.
</P>
<P>
Said areas have already collected 16,135 pieces of clothing and
quilts, including over 8.3 million cotton items. The bulk of the
relief materials will be distributed in northeast China, with a
small portion earmarked for distribution in areas along the
Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The ministry issued a circular on Monday calling for other
provinces and municipalities to mount donation campaigns. The list
excludes flood ravaged areas such as Jiangxi, Hunan, Hubei,
Heilongjiang, Fujian, Jilin, Anhui and Sichuan provinces,
Chongqing Municipality and the Inner Mongolia and Guangxi Zhuang
autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
The circular requires relevant provinces and municipalities to
list donated goods in nine categories -- grain, food, medical
supplies, bottled water and water purification equipment,
construction materials, machinery and electrical equipment,
communication equipment, agricultural production materials and
miscellaneous items. The ministry must grant approval prior to
the shipment of relief supplies to flood-ravaged areas.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Municipality and Zhejiang, Henan, Guangdong, Shaanxi,
Shanxi, Hainan and Jiangsu provinces will provide winter clothing
and quilts for flood victims in areas along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The ministry and the State Economic and Trade Commission have
ordered 100,000 cotton camps, 100,000 pieces of cotton
clothing and 900,000 cotton quilts from domestic factories and
will distribute related items in northeast China at the earliest
possible date.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
