<HEADLINE> Iran: Taliban Responsible for Iranian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Iran warned the Afghan Taliban
militia Tuesday not to evade responsibility for the fate and
safety of the Iranian diplomats allegedly kidnaped by the group.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi made the warning
after the Taliban leader Mullah Mohammad Omar denied Monday night
having information about the whereabouts of 11 captured Iranian
diplomats and a reporter of the official IRNA news agency.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Tuesday, one of Omar's close aides Mullah Hassan
Qalchei said in Dubai that the captured Iranians "are in good
health and kept in a prison near Qandahar in southern
Afghanistan," the IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Such contradictory and ambiguous remarks are not acceptable to
the Islamic Republic of Iran, Mohammadi said, Tehran holds the
Taliban responsible for the safety of the Iranians.
</P>
<P>
Such remarks also run counter to what Pakistani officials have
told Iranian authorities on behalf of the Taliban, he said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan is widely believed in support of the Taliban, a
student militia, which seized the capital Kabul in 1996 and has
gained control of most of Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi said that prior to the capture of Mazari Sharif in
northern Afghanistan, where the Iranian diplomats were captured,
the Pakistani government has informed the Taliban of the presence
of the Iranian diplomats in Iran's consulate general.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani officials have also assured Iran of the safety of the
Iranian diplomats, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Iran has called on the United Nations
and the International Committee of the Red Cross to dispatch a
fact-finding mission to Afghanistan to get information about the
whereabouts of the Iranian nationals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
