<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- IBM China/Hong Kong Limited
announced here Tuesday a suite of Business Intelligence (BI)
solutions, which can give businessmen customized, cost-effective
ways to consolidate and organize all their data.
</P>
<P>
The solutions can help businessmen get the information they
need and then help them make faster and smarter business
decisions, said Anita Au, manager of Business Intelligence
solutions of IBM Greater China Group.
</P>
<P>
For the solutions, IBM offers hardware platforms with high
scalability, software products and consulting and services.
Together they form the three inter-linked stages of application:
data warehousing, data mining and decision support.
</P>
<P>
"BI is the process of transforming data generated during the
course of doing business into useful knowledge," Au said.
</P>
<P>
It helps to analyze the current existing data to identify
meaningful relationships within seemingly unrelated data, she
said.
</P>
<P>
"By consolidating data and analyzing data with speed and
accuracy, it enhances better business decisions and to gain
competitive edge," Au added.
</P>
<P>
IBM opened for business in Hong Kong on April 16, 1957.
