<DOCNO> XIE19980901.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Foreign Reserves Remain World's 3rd Largest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's official foreign
currency assets stood at 96.5 billion U.S. dollars at the end of
July 1998, ranking the third largest in the world after Japan and
the Chinese mainland, the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the foreign currency assets, which stayed the same level as
at the end of June, 77.8 billion U.S. dollars were held in the
Exchange Fund and 18.7 billion U.S. dollars in the Land Fund.
</P>
<P>
The total foreign currency assets represent about eight times
the currency in circulation or about 44 percent of Hong Kong
dollar M3, one of the highest ratios in the world, said the HKMA,
the de facto central bank of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Japan topped the rank with 207.5 billion U.S. dollars while the
Chinese mainland making the second with 140.6 billion U.S.
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
