<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Tenth Macao International
Fireworks Display Contest will be held from mid-September to early
October, a tourism official said at a press conference here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Joao Costa Antunes, director of the Macao Government Tourist
Office, said that ten teams from Taiwan, Germany, Britain,
Thailand, Australia, Canada, China's Mainland, Spain, Portugal and
Japan will take part in the contest.
</P>
<P>
The teams will give fireworks shows on the nights of September
12, 19, 26 and October 1 and 5. Every two teams will share one
night.
</P>
<P>
Macao International Fireworks Display Contest was launched in
1989. Each time in the first six contests, five teams
participated. And the number of teams rose to ten beginning from
1995.
</P>
<P>
It is said that a total of 50 tons of powder will be consumed
this time. 
