<HEADLINE> EMC Striving for Greater Market Share In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- EMC Corp., a computer memory
systems maker in the United States, opened a representative office
in Shanghai today.
</P>
<P>
It is the second representative office for EMC in China. The
first one, which is in Beijing, was established in 1996.
</P>
<P>
EMC products have now been widely used in many Chinese
enterprises and organizations, as well as by many transnational
companies in China since the products were first introduced to the
Chinese market in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Robert Dutkowsky, senior vice-president of EMC, who was here in
Shanghai for the occasion, said sustained economic growth had
brought great market potential to China, and the prime work of EMC
is to establish a solid foundation in China.
</P>
<P>
Dutkowsky said he hoped that his company's products would make
up 40 percent of China's high-performance digital memory systems
market in three years.
</P>
<P>
EMC will set up its third representative office in south
China's Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong Province, by the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
EMC chalked up about 3 billion U.S. dollars in business volume
globally in 1997. 
</P>
