<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed broadly lower Tuesday on heavy
selling in the afternoon session.
</P>
<P>
The heavy selling took place after the government announced
foreign exchange controls measures earlier Tuesday to curb
speculation in the ringgit in a move to insulate its economy from
risks and vulnerabilities caused by external developments,
analysts said.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index dropped
40.21 points, or 13.27 percent, breaching the 300-point mark, to
262.70, the all-share Emas Index lost 7.95 points to 71.60, the
Industrial Index dropped 93.75 points to 545.69 and the Second
Board Index fell 1.53 points to 75.30.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers 431 to 121 while 135 counters were
unchanged, 233 untraded and 38 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover rose to 226.653 million shares valued
at 415.995 million ringgit (about 106.665 million U.S. dollars)
from 131.362 million shares worth 205.862 million ringgit (about
52.785 million U.S. dollars) traded last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover increased to 222.222 million shares
valued at 411.959 million ringgit (about 105.63 million U.S.
dollars) from 126.830 million valued at 4.532 million ringgit
(about 1.162 million U.S. dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover decreased to 4.432 million shares
valued at 4.035 million ringgit (about 1.034 million U.S.
dollars) from last Friday's 4.532 million shares valued at 4.539
million ringgit (about 1.163 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover increased to 3.240 million shares valued at
7.626 million ringgit (about 1.955 million U.S. dollars) from last
Friday's 2.080 million shares valued at 6.365 million ringgit
(about 1.632 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 7.113
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
18.389 million shares, construction 21.080 million shares,
trade/services 98.735 million shares, infrastructures 1.804
million shares, finance 48.528 million shares, hotels 423,000
shares, properties 10.832 million shares, plantation 9.428 million
shares, mining 916,000 shares, trusts 79,000 shares, closed/fund
15,000 shares and loans 4.881 million shares. 
</P>
