<HEADLINE> European Union Program Going Smoothly in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A large European Union-funded
program has been making progress in the Tibet Autonomous Region
and, once finished, will greatly promote the region's agricultural
production, said a local official.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 180 million yuan (20 million U.S. dollars)
has been invested in the program that emphasizes low-yield land
improvements and water conservation projects in a local grain
production center.
</P>
<P>
The official said that since 1994, nearly 6,660 hectares of
economic forests has been planted and the grain output of another
2,600 hectares has been increased by more than 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Some 82.46 million yuan more in funding is expected in upcoming
months, and the program is scheduled to be completed in 2003,
according to the official.  
</P>
