<HEADLINE> Hong Kong TV Corporations Donate to Students in Flooded Areas (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China Youth Development
Foundation, which has worked for nine years to help school
dropouts, today received nine million HK dollars from two Hong
Kong TV corporations, which will be used to help students in the
flooded areas continue their studies.
</P>
<P>
Most Chinese schools begin the new semester today.
</P>
<P>
Since early this summer, a dozen provinces in the Yangtze River
Basin and along northeast China's Nenjiang and Songhua River
Basins have suffered the worst flooding in decades.
</P>
<P>
Schools in the flood-stricken areas were seriously
damaged. Latest statistics show that in the 10 provinces most
severely hit by the floods, such as Hunan Province, nearly 45,000
schools have been ravaged and about 8.5 million students are
without normal school facilities.
</P>
<P>
About three million square meters of schoolhouses collapsed,
and another 7.47 million square meters were declared unsafe after
the flooding.
</P>
<P>
The direct losses to all of these schools are estimated at some
7.6 billion RMB yuan (nearly one billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
