<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Securities Market Idle Amid Political Uncertainty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Transactions in the Russian
stock market tapered to almost zero Tuesday as traders try to come
to terms with the country's political uncertainty.
</P>
<P>
No deals were made on the Russian Trading System early Tuesday
as President Boris Yeltsin resubmitted his nomination of Viktor
Chernomyrdin as prime minister.
</P>
<P>
But Gennady Seleznyov, speaker of the State Duma, or lower
house of parliament, said the nomination would be shot down in the
second round of voting.
</P>
<P>
Quotations for leading stocks shed 15 percent to 30 percent in
the first 20 minutes, the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The RTS-Interfax Composite Index in rubles, however, actually
rose by 12.55 percent to 23.6 by 11:25 local time (07:25 GMT), as
exchange rate for the ruble against foreign currencies further
plummeted.
</P>
<P>
The RTS-Interfax Composite Index in dollars fell by 4.68
percent to 15.07.
</P>
<P>
Market operators said that despite some half-hearted attempts
to adjust quotations, most traders were waiting for events to
unfold.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma overwhelmingly rejected Chernomyrdin's
candidacy Monday night. He won only 94 votes for the presidential
motion while 251 deputies voted against him. The nominee needs 226
votes in the 450-seat Duma to win approval.
</P>
<P>
Plunges in world stock markets, partly a result of Russia's
financial crisis, further dampened the Russian markets.
</P>
<P>
By 11:20 local time (07:20 GMT), the RTS quoted Unified Energy
Systems of Russia at 0.022/0.028 dollars, down 30 percent from
Monday's close. Stocks of Lukoil, Russia's largest oil company,
fell by 11.1 percent to 3.35/3.65 dollars. Mosenergo declined by
15 percent to 0.013/0.0135 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Gazprom shares, which shot up dramatically last week following
the return of Chernomyrdin, who is former boss of Gas Monopoly-
Gazprom, also slid Tuesday because of the State Duma's continued
blocking of his nomination.
</P>
<P>
Gazprom shed 10.3 percent to the bottom line of its trading
band of 0.91 rubles in the first few minutes on the Moscow Stock
Exchange. A total of 786,000 shares were traded by noon.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, regular trading in the Moscow
Interbank Currency Exchange (MICEX) remained suspended Tuesday,
and authorities said it would not resume until after Thursday.
</P>
<P>
However, the MICEX will continue to deal in U.S. dollars in the
electronic lot trading regime.
</P>
<P>
The MICEX's Council was planning to adopt an electronic system
for setting exchange rates used by world exchanges, Interfax
reported.
</P>
<P>
Electronic fixing is seen as more flexible in determining the
dollar's exchange rate without the participation of the Central
Bank, which until recently has to react to commercial banks' needs
in case of sharp imbalance between demand and supply.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the new system, the MICEX fixing will be
calculated on the basis of the average rate of the deals concluded
by banks in a trading session in approximately 5-10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
After MICEX sets the exchange rate, banks will be allowed to
make additional transactions at the announced exchange rate.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
