<HEADLINE> Nigerian Football Players Die as Boat Capsizes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Attempts to recover the bodies
of the 13 Nigerian football players and their coach were still
going on by Tuesday, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The fourteen people were drowned when the boat they were
traveling in capsized last Sunday in south Nigeria's Delta State.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 8:00 p.m. when the players and
coach of the Ronaldo Football Club were returning from a friendly
match at Steel Town, Aladja in the Delta State, in which they
won, media reports said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Eight players swam to safety and were saved.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said the boat did not go far from the bank when
the driver demanded an increased fare from 10 to 20 Naira (0.12
to 0.24 U.S. Dollars), citing fuel shortage as the reason.
</P>
<P>
It was learned that the players were angered by the move and
argued with the driver, when the latter tried to reverse the boat
to the bank and caused the accident. 
