<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Robbery Attempt in Thailand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Three men were shot dead in an
attempted payroll robbery outside a hotel in Pattaya, a beach
resort more than 200 kilometers southeast of Bangkok, a police
source said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Pattaya police had been tipped off about the plot to snatch
the 1.3-million-baht (about 32,000 U.S. dollars) payroll of the
Town Hotel on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Plainclothes policemen replaced the payroll staff after the
money was withdrawn and drove to the hotel. When the robbers
blocked the way to snatch the money, the policemen tried to make
arrests. But the robbers resisted with gun fire, wounding one
policeman.
</P>
<P>
The policemen returned fire, killing three robbers on the spot.
Police later arrested a hotel worker suspected of collaborating
with the robbers. 
