<BODY>
<HEADLINE> APPEC '98 Due to Be Held in Singapore This Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 1 (Xinhua) - The 14th Asia Pacific
Petroleum Conference (APPEC '98) is due to be held here on
September 14-16, 1998, with the theme "The Asian Oil &AMP; Gas Market:
Aftermath of the Financial Meltdown", according to its organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,000 top executives and professionals from the oil
industry are expected to attend the three-day event and focus
their discussions on how to ensure business continuity and
viability when the economic and financial turmoil plaguing Asian
countries has had a far-reaching impact on the oil and gas
industries.
</P>
<P>
The participants are also expected to debate some key issues
which post great challenges to the industry under the existing
business environment characteristic of intensifying competition.
</P>
<P>
The main topics on agenda include companies restructuring,
business opportunities, strategies and infrastructure needed to
improve profitability.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Trade and Industry of Singapore Lee Yock Suan will
inaugurate the APPEC '98 that will feature four ministerial
speakers.
</P>
<P>
President of the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries
Conference Obaid bin Said al-Nasseri, who is the Minister for
Petroleum &AMP; Mineral Resources of the United Arab Emirates, will
give a Ministerial Keynote address.
</P>
<P>
Ministerial Delegates from Indonesia, China, Australia will
also address the conference.
</P>
<P>
APPEC is an event held every year since 1985 and has become a
focal meeting point for the oil industry in Asia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
