<HEADLINE> Trade Fair Opens in Urumqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Over 4,000 businesspeople from
32 countries and regions are attending a trade fair which opened
in this capital city of the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region today.
</P>
<P>
The eight-day Seventh Urumqi Economic and Trade Fair has attracted
over 4,000 large and medium-sized Chinese enterprises, and
Xinjiang -- the host -- is offering over 90 projects to
overseas investors, and over 110 projects to domestic investors.
</P>
<P>
As restructuring of state-owned enterprises reaches a crucial
stage in China, the trading of property rights has become a new
feature at this year's Urumqi fair, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Zhou, vice chairman of the Xinjiang Fair, as
one of the major regional trade fairs in China, the current event
has already become an important show-window and a bridge linking
China with the world, especially the countries of the Commonwealth
of Independent States and other neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
"The fair is of special significance since it is held amid the
Asian financial crisis and economic volatility in Russia,"
the vice chairman said.
</P>
<P>
The previous six fairs had combined transactions of 9.144
billion U.S. dollars from overseas investors, and 25.39 billion
yuan (3.596 billion U.S. dollars) from domestic investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
