<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on US Missile Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China consistently and firmly
objects to any forms of terrorism, and strongly condemns all
terrorist acts aimed at innocent civilians including the
explosions in Kenya and Tanzania, according to Chinese Foreign
Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao at a regular news conference here
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks in response to a reporter's question on
China's comment on the recent US missile attack toward Sudan and
Afghanistan, saying that China is "concerned about the post-attack
situation in the two countries".
</P>
<P>
China advocates opposing terrorism in accordance with the
principles of the United Nations Charter and international rules,
on the basis of respecting a country's sovereignty and territorial
integrity, and through joint efforts of the international
community, Zhu said, adding that this is "an effective approach to
solving and exterminating terrorism." 
</P>
</TEXT>
