<HEADLINE> Angola Suspends UNITA Members' Function in Govt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government has
announced the suspension of the National Union for the Total
Independence of Angola@P;9Q%j5DIM2U9
Q%=9J\"!rh%=915~
unity and reconciliation government, effective from Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The govern said in a communique that the decision will
last until UNITA complies with all clauses stipulated in the
Lusaka peace accord signed in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Angola national assembly Speaker Roberto de Almeida
also proposed to the Supreme Court to suspend UNITA members'
positions in parliament.
</P>
<P>
However, the government still pledged in the communique that
it will continue "to adhere to all that is contained in the
Lusaka peace protocol perfectly in a bid to achieve national
unity and reconciliation."
</P>
<P>
It also appeal to the Angolan people to keep calm and alert,
and refrain from any moves in violation of the spirit of national
unity and reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government has been accusing the opposition UNITA
of delaying to carry out the tasks prescribed for the final
stages of the peace deal by refusing to disarm all its forces or
hand over four central cities under its control.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have been attacking each other on the issues for
the past months, bringing the peace process in the country to a
serious standstill.
</P>
<P>
To make matters worse, the former rebel UNITA movement
announced on August 24 to cease its cooperation with the troika
observer missions, namely Russia, Portugal and the United States.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the government move to suspend UNITA members'
official function might further worsen the crisis. 
</P>
