<HEADLINE> Fujian Industrial Bank Reports Rapid Asset Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The asset value of Fujian
Industrial Bank, China's first joint-stock commercial bank, has
reached 39.9 billion yuan (4.8 billion US dollars), according to
the latest official figures.
</P>
<P>
The amount represents an average annual growth rate of 38
percent since the bank was founded 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics also indicate that the bank's capital
volume has soared from 600 million yuan to 3.38 billion yuan
during the period.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, the bank has reaped 3.1 billion yuan in
profits, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the bank has 225 operations in Fujian and other
parts of China, including two branches in Shanghai and Shenzhen
and one representative office in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The bank has focused its loans mainly on projects in Fujian,
with a total value of nearly 100 billion yuan. In the first half
of this year, the bank issued a total of 10.5 billion yuan in
loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
