<HEADLINE> APEC to Launch Women Business Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The APEC (Asian-Pacific
Economic Cooperation) Women's Business Council will be launched
Wednesday at the two-day 1998 APEC Women Leaders' Network meeting
which began here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Minister of International Trade and Industry Rafidah
Aziz suggested at the meeting that the Council came up with
programs to motivate women entrepreneurs to invest in APEC member
economies.
</P>
<P>
The business council should ensure that within each APEC
economy, there is business-support mechanism and facilities that
can assist women entrepreneurs to venture into the market whether
in trade or industry, Rafidah said.
</P>
<P>
She said the business council should also pursue the
establishment of the APEC Women's trade-net to optimize the
benefit of electronic commerce and strengthen the existing
network.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should also be put into market-driven human resource
and entrepreneur development programs, she said.
</P>
<P>
This can serve to promote the region as a profitable
manufacturing and export base and benefit manufacturers from the
region, she said.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference, attended by some 230 participants from
APEC members, will mainly discuss the current economic crisis and
its impact on women.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the conference organizing committee Nor Azah Awin
said women would also like to play their roles to help revive the
economy in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
