<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Fujian Invests More in Fixed Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 1 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
increased its investment in fixed assets in the first half of this
year, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Fujian invested 30.3 billion yuan (3.65 billion US dollars) in
fixed assets in the first seven months of this year, a jump of
37.7 percent from the same period last year. The growth rate,
which is 22.1 percentage points higher than the national average
during the same period, is the third highest among all provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown shows that Fujian invested 14 billion yuan (1.69
billion US dollars) in infrastructure in the first seven months, a
surge of 56.3 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
In another analysis, overseas funds worth 7.3 billion yuan was
invested in fixed assets during the January-July period, which is
59 percent more than a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
