<HEADLINE> Tung Chee-hwa Visits Shenzhen to Strengthen Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee-hwa, chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR)
reportedly visited Shenzhen Monday for talks to promote economic
ties between the SAR and the special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
"Both sides deem that the chief executive's visit was very
successful," a government official said today. "It helped enhance
mutual understanding and cooperation."
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Shenzhen, Tung said that Shenzhen is the
first interior city he has visited since taking office on July 1,
1997. He expressed his hope that the leaders of the two sides
could conduct more exchanges to strengthen mutual understanding in
the future.
</P>
<P>
Tung also expressed his gratitude for the support given to Hong
Kong by the central, Guangdong and Shenzhen governments when its
new airport encountered difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Zhang Gaoli, deputy Communist Party chief of
Guangdong and Party chief of Shenzhen, Tung visited the Shenzhen
High-tech Industrial Park and the Huangtian International Airport.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Gaoli expressed his confidence in enhancing the economic
cooperation between Shenzhen and Hong Kong in the fields of
infrastructure, new-tech development, the management and service
of ports of entry, financial operations, and smuggling and
drug-trafficking.  
</P>
