<HEADLINE> Panama President Appoints New Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 31 (Xinhua) -- President of Panama Ernesto
Perez Balladares on Monday appointed Eduardo Ritter as the new
minister of foreign affairs to replace Ricardo Alberto Arias.
</P>
<P>
The presidential press office announced that President
Balladares accepted Arias's resignation on the day and shifted
Ritter, minister of state for canal affairs, to the post of
foreign affairs minister.
</P>
<P>
But Arias will remain in office until September 7 when Chilean
President Eduardo Frei concludes his visit to Panama.
</P>
<P>
Frei is scheduled to start a state visit to Panama at the
beginning of September and attend the 12th summit meeting of the
12-nation Rio Group.
</P>
<P>
Arias submitted his resignation last week partly because of
health problem, A Ministry of Foreign Affairs spokesman said on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
But the main reason for his decision to quit is that the
Panama-U.S. negotiations on setting up a multinational
anti-narcotics center in a U.S. Air Force base after the
U.S. forces pull out in the year 2000 have run into deadlock, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Since January this year, the two countries have failed to
resume the talks on the issue, which began in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
