<HEADLINE> New York Group to Set Up Trade Center in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition and trade center
will be set up in north China's largest port city for New York's
small businesses to display their products.
</P>
<P>
The center will be located in the Tianjin New Technological
Industrial Park, according to an agreement signed last week
between the park's management committee and the New York Small
Business Development Center (NYSBDC).
</P>
<P>
With 22 local branches, the NYSBDC supervises more than 30,000
small businesses in the State of New York, making it the largest
small business development center in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin's business circles are expected to get more chances to
cooperate with small firms in New York and attract more investment
through the exhibition center.
</P>
<P>
The center also should help these American firms explore the
market here by showing their latest technology and products.
</P>
<P>
James L. King, state director of the NYSBDC who signed the
agreement on behalf of the American group, called the center a
"showcase" for both sides to step up efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
