<HEADLINE> Beijing Attracting Transnational Corporations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- World-famous international
corporations such as Motorola Inc. and Samson Company had set up
82 exclusively invested corporations in Beijing by the end of this
June, according to the latest report from the Beijing Municipal
Government.
</P>
<P>
By the end of June, 323 transnational corporations, among which
148 are listed in the global top 500, had invested in 434 projects
in Beijing with a foreign capital volume of 3.63 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, 28 international corporations
including Tokyo Menka Kaisha Ltd. and the Du Pont Company invested
250 million U.S. dollars in 30 new projects in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Japan Daiichi Medicine Co., Ltd. joined Beijing Medicine
Corp. to set up Daiichi Medicine (Beijing) Co., Ltd. with an
investment of 29.5 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the major attraction of Beijing lies in its
improving market conditions and its growing high-technology
environment.
</P>
<P>
With the increasing investment on the mainland, more and more
foreign companies have moved their China headquarters from Hong
Kong to Beijing, the experts said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
