<HEADLINE> Albanian President Calls for Prevention of Social Turmoil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep Mejdani
Monday called for an end to the politicizing of every event and
urged a renewed respect for law in order to achieve peaceful
co-existence and prevent turmoil in the country.
</P>
<P>
Albania is again being threatened by social unrest as the
opposition, led by the Democratic Party (DP), have been reacting
strongly to the arrest on August 22 of six senior officials of the
former DP government on charges of crimes against humanity.
</P>
<P>
"A return to the old way of an eye for an eye will lead
nowhere. It benefits no one and it does not help fulfill
obligations required of us related to the Kosovo issue. Neither
does it help our efforts to build and strengthen a legal state and
set up a modern constitution," the president said in the port city
of Durres.
</P>
<P>
"We must respect the separation of judiciary from
administration," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Affirming that he encourages dialogue, debates and
confrontation of ideas, as well as mutual understanding between
parties, Mejdani urged all political forces to be "more ethical,
more mature, more patient and more respectful to each other."
</P>
<P>
He also called for a transparent, standardized, speedy and
supervised trial of the six former officials to avoid unnecessary
turmoil.
</P>
<P>
This was the first presidential comment on the growing tension
in the country. The Albanian media have lately criticized
Mejdani's silence over the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
