<HEADLINE> Clinton Arrives in Moscow for Summit With Yeltsin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 1 (Xinhua) -- United States President Bill
Clinton arrived here Tuesday to meet Russian President Boris
Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
Clinton was met at the airport by Acting Premier Viktor
Chernomyrdin and other senior Russian officials.
</P>
<P>
Clinton and Yeltsin are to meet Tuesday and Wednesday for their
first full-scale summit since March 1997. Since then, they have
met briefly a few times, most recently in May, when both were in
Birmingham, England.
</P>
<P>
The two will focus on security and Russia's economic
crisis. Clinton said Russia can count on American support so long
as it stays the course to reform.
</P>
<P>
Local media opinions hold that the ill-timed summit will not
achieve any significant concrete results because of the present
situation.
</P>
<P>
Clinton's authority is being threatened unprecedentedly by his
"inappropriate relationship" with former White House intern Monica
Lewinsky.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's popularity has fallen to the lowest point since he
became Russian president in 1991, and he has been asked to step
down by the parliament chiefly because of the worsening economic
situation of Russia.
</P>
<P>
Clinton will travel to Ireland and the British province of
Northern Ireland after his trip to Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
