<HEADLINE> Rare Birds Found in Indonesia's East Kalimantan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A research team has found an
endangered bird species in the Kutai hinterland in Indonesia's
East Kalimantan province, the Jakarta Post reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The rare species was found accidentally by the research team
which was studying jungle fowl, head of the local conservation
office Ade Rahmat said.
</P>
<P>
"The discovery is surprising because the species was only
thought to be in Vietnam and was considered extinct in other parts
of the world," Ade added. 
