<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0500 GMT, September 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The Clinton Administration tried to assure
investors Monday that the United States economy is basically sound
despite the second biggest points plunge in Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin said he had talked to President
Bill Clinton, who was on Air Force One on his way to Moscow for a
summit with Russian leaders, after Monday's stock market closed
with the Dow Jones industrial average down more than 512 points.
</P>
<P>
"The fundamentals of the United States economy are strong due
in part to the sound policies we've been following," Rubin stated.
</P>
<P>
"The prospects for growth, low unemployment and low inflation
continue to be strong," he said.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said he had also spoken to Federal Reserve Chairman Alan
Greenspan and officials around the world. (US-Investors)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- The Dow Jones industrials suffered their
second-biggest point loss ever Monday, amid news of a
parliamentary showdown in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Dow blue-chip industrial index lost 512.61 points to close
at 7,539.07. It was just under the memorable loss of October 19,
1987. It lost more than 6 percent on the day, wiping out all of
its gains for the year and nearly 20 percent below its all-time
closing high last July 17 of 9,337.97. The Dow ended 1997 at
7,908.25.
</P>
<P>
In Russia, the Boris Yeltsin's choice for prime minister was
disapproved in the parliament, despite Russia's growing economic
crisis. It was reported that President Clinton left Washington for
a summit meeting with President Boris Yeltsin to talk about
"reforms." (New York, Stocks Plunge)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesia posted a 69.12 percent inflation in the
first eight months this year, the Central Statistics Agency
announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The inflation rate in August was 6.3 percent, much higher than
the corresponding period of last year which stood at 0.88 percent,
said the agency's chief Sugito Suwito.
</P>
<P>
Sugito said the main cause of the higher inflation was a 2.45
percent increase in foods price.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the inflation rate for the whole year would
reach as high as 80 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country's inflation rate was 11.05 percent Last year.
Indonesia-Inflation (Indonesia-Inflation) 
</P>
</TEXT>
