<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Poland in
the first half of 1998 reached a record high of 5 billion U.S.
dollars, the Polish foreign investment administration reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment in Poland amounted to 5.7 billion dollars in
the whole of last year compared with 5.2 billion dollars in 1996
and 2.5 billion dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The figures are based on official statistics related to
projects each with investment of more than one million dollars.
</P>
<P>
So far, Italy's Fiat Group boasts the biggest investment in
Poland with 1.247 billion dollars, followed by South Korea's
Daewoo Corporation, with 1.200 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The increase of foreign investment in Poland is chiefly
attributed to the stable political situation, sustained rapid
economic growth and favorable policy on attracting investment to
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
