<HEADLINE>   Domestic Investments High in Argentine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's domestic
investments exceeded two billion U.S. dollars in the first eight
months this year, an official report said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The investments are being used to enlarge and improve the
production capacity of 63 plants, including the telecommunications
enterprise NEXTEL, which has invested 100 million dollars in
opening a new Customer Service Center.
</P>
<P>
Among major beneficiaries of the investments are an asphalt
plant in San Lorenzo and a milk plant which have recieved 92
million dollars and 57 million dollars respectively, the report
said. 
</P>
