<HEADLINE> China's First Ethnic Dress Museum Opens in Guizhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China's first ethnic dress
museum displaying costumes of the Miao Nationality has been set up
in this capital of southwest China's Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 3,000 ethnic costumes and ornaments on
display in the museum featuring the different development periods
of the 5,000-year-old ethnic group.
</P>
<P>
As the fourth largest ethnic group in China, the Miao
nationality is famous for wax-printing dresses and silver
ornaments.
</P>
<P>
The province has recently set up a series of cultural and art
museums about the ethnic group's special social customs, ethnic
dresses and wedding ceremonies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
