<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Crisis Must Be Solved by Russia: Austrian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia's financial crisis can
only be solved by Russia itself, Austrian Foreign Minister
Wolfgang Schoessel said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Schoessel, who also heads the European Union's Foreign
Ministers Council, said the international community could ask
Russia to continue its reforms and create conditions for
cooperation with foreign countries and international institutions,
but external forces alone could not resolve the Russian issues.
</P>
<P>
He called for an early return to stability in Russia, warning
that Moscow's plans to overcome the financial crisis contained
certain "disturbing" elements, such as restrictions over the
reform and privatization process, and resumption of state control
on prices and foreign exchange transactions.
</P>
<P>
He urged Russia to speed up banking reforms to ensure the
safety and participation of Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
