<HEADLINE> China's First Computer Translation Program for Tibetan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
developed a computer program that translates Tibetan into Chinese
and English.
</P>
<P>
Research and development for the program was initiated four
years ago by a group of computer scientists and linguists from the
Teachers University of Qinghai Province in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, these scientists have developed an electronic
dictionary, information base, and grammar analysis system related
to the program.
</P>
<P>
With 42,000 word entries, including 27,000 special words and
phrases, the system can translate at a speed of 162
words per minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
