<HEADLINE> Spain's Trade Deficit Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Spain registered a trade
deficit of 9.73 billion U.S. dollars in the first half this year,
a 21.9 percent increase over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The Trade Ministry attributed the increased deficit to more
imports. In the first six months, Spain's exports totaled 56.06
billion dollars while the imports amounted to 65.8 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, Spain registed an adverse balance of
trade of 3.18 billion dollars with the European Union nations, a
37.3 percent increase over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the government would step up measures to
reduce the trade deficit. 
</P>
