<DOCNO> XIE19980901.0263 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oil Sector to Push Toward 8 percent National Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The State Petrochemical
Industry Bureau (SPIB) is expected to take measures to ensure the
reeling petrochemical industry, and this helps meet a national
economic growth target of 8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, SPIB released a statement, outlining major tasks
intended to be achieved by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
SPIB will organize a special team to supervise implementation
of State-adjusted oil production and processing plans in the third
and fourth quarters, which have been carried out by China National
Petroleum Corp (CNPC) and China Petrochemical Corp (Sinopec).
</P>
<P>
The bureau will try to implement the State-set oil price
structure and to guide the two groups in buying and selling crude
oil and refined oil products at prices set by the State Planning
Commission. The measures are expected to bring order to a
competitive market.
</P>
<P>
The national industrial administration is working with customs
authorities to crack down on refined oil product smuggling, a move
crucial for guaranteeing reductions in stockpiles of crude oil and
refined oil products, both by 3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The central government required the two petrochemical groups to
realize 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) in profits this
year, a target that has been downgraded in view of a sharp
worldwide drop in oil prices and because of the costs of
industrial restructuring.
</P>
<P>
The bureau urged the chemical enterprises to enhance sales
promotion and to explore more intensely markets both at home and
abroad.
</P>
<P>
They have been asked to ensure profits in the sector of between
1.5 billion yuan (180 million US dollars) and 2 billion yuan (240
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The chemical fertilizer market is likely to pick up as the
demand of farmers in the flood-stricken areas for fertilizer will
surge after flood waters recede.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
