<HEADLINE> Public Security Bureaus Contribute to Flood Control Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A senior officer with the
Ministry of Public Security has disclosed that related
departments had rescued some 442,000 flood victims, helped
evacuate more than 3.48 million people, and safeguarded public and
personal property valued at over 1.2 billion yuan by August 20.
</P>
<P>
Public security bureaus in China's flood-ravaged areas,
especially those in the Yangtze, Nenjiang and Songhua river valleys,
assigned some 185,000 officers to flood control efforts between
early June and August 10. Two officers sacrificed their lives and
3,493 officers sustained injuries in related efforts.
</P>
<P>
Public security bureaus have sustained losses of over 210
million yuan, with floods destroying 1,492 automobiles, 1,446
motorcycles, 74 boats, 3,791 pieces of telecommunications equipment
and public buildings covering 293,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Nonetheless, related departments are working around the clock
to fight crime and ensure a good social environment for flood
victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
