<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russian Crisis to Affect Indonesia, Says Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Russia's deepening financial
crisis will affect Indonesia's economy, a senior minister was
quoted by the Indonesian Observer Tuesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
The effect of the Russian crisis on the Indonesian economy
could be seen from the stock and money markets, said Coordinating
Minister of Economy, Finance and Industry Ginandjar Kartasasmita.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's bourse reacted negatively to the suspension of the
ruble trading after the Russian currency plunged 29 percent last
week, with the Jakarta Composite Index tumbling 4.5 percent to a
year-low.
</P>
<P>
The bourse was sharply down in midday trading Monday before it
rebounded in late trading on a rise in PT Telekomunikasi
Indonesia, Jakarta's market bellwether which accounts for almost
20 percent of the benchmark index.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah, although continuing its upward bound journey with
the assistance of the inflow of foreign aid and loans, failed to
break the psychological level of 11,000 per U.S. dollar as
expected by analysts last week because of regional weakness
triggered by the Russian woes.
</P>
<P>
The rupiah on the Jakarta inter-bank spot market was closed on
Monday at 11,050 against the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
"We must be cautious and watch the developments in Russia very
closely, because long-term problems in Russia will affect
Indonesia," Ginandjar said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian turmoil may affect the world economy as a whole,
and will certainly affect Indonesia's exports, he added.
</P>
<P>
Just like Indonesia, Russia has also turned to the
International Monetary Fund (IMF) for a bailout package after the
country was hit by currency turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Ginandjar said he would discuss Russian developments with IMF
deputy managing director Stanley Fischer and Asia-Pacific director
Hubert Neiss, who are scheduled to visit Indonesia on September 18
and September 3 respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
