<HEADLINE> Hingis Wins Opener at U.S. Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 31 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina
Hingis of Switzerland opened her bid to defend title smoothly
today by beating Polish qualifier Aleksandra Olsza in straight
sets easily on the first day of U.S. Open tennis championships.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old top seed only needed 59 minutes to breeze past
Olsza with a 6-2, 6-0 victory. It is Hingis' eighth straight win
