<HEADLINE> Sampras Rolls over Goellner in U.S. Open Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Top seeded Pete Sampras of the
United States dispatched Marc-Kevin Goellner in straight sets in
the first round of the U.S. Open tennis championships here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who ranks first in the world, beat the German 6-3,
6-2,6-2 in one hour and 24 minutes to improve his record to
140-26 in Grand Slams and 48-6 at the Open. The 27-year-old
American hit 38 aces during the lop-sided match.
</P>
<P>
Goellner, who had lost in the first round of 22 tournaments in
1998, was beaten eight times in nine games in Grand Slams.
Today,the unseeded player made 25 unforced errors.
</P>
<P>
Sampras, who has won five Wimbledon and two Australian Open
titles, is seeking his fifth U.S. Open championship to tie former
Australian star Roy Emerson's record for career Grand Slam
titles.He also is looking to tie fellow American Jinny Connors'
modern-day record of five U.S. Open titles. 
