<HEADLINE> IMF Okays Third Annual ESAF Loan for Niger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) announced here Monday the approval of the third annual
loan for Niger under the Enhanced Structural Adjustment Facility
(ESAF), equivalent to about 26 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The loan is provided in support of the government's program for
1998-99. The loan is available in two equal semiannual
installments, the first of which is available immediately.
</P>
<P>
The principal macroeconomic objectives for 1998-2001 are to
achieve real GDP growth of 4 to 5 percent a year, maintain
inflation in the 2 to 4 percent range, and reduce the overall
fiscal deficit to 5.2 percent of GDP in 2000 from 7.5 percent in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Within this medium-term strategy, Niger's program for 1998-99,
projects real GDP growth of 4.5 percent, maintaining year-end
inflation at about 3 percent, and an external current account
deficit at 9.4 percent of GDP in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Niger joined the IMF in April 1963. Its quota is about 64
million dollars. As the end of June, this year, Niger's
outstanding use of IMF resources totaled about 64 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
