<HEADLINE> Kohl Stresses Importance to Keep Stability in Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
Monday said that a stable Russia is of great importance for
Germany.
</P>
<P>
"Peace, progress and stability in Russia are also peace,
progress and stability in Germany," said Kohl at an election
campaign rally of his Christian Democratic Union party in Hanover.
</P>
<P>
The German chancellor on Monday also called on European
countries to make joint effort to prevent the Russian crisis from
worsening.
</P>
<P>
If Russia backed down from its political and economic reforms,
peace and stability in Europe was at stake, Kohl said.
</P>
<P>
German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel also said Monday that
Germany would continue to support Russia despite its current
crisis.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the nomination of Viktor
Chernomyrdin as Russian prime minister could still be approved by
the Russian State Duma, the lower house of parliament, but he also
stressed that he did not want to interfere in Russia's internal
affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
