<HEADLINE> Greek, French Leaders Discuss Russian Economic Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 31 (Xinhua) -- The Premiers of Greece and French
ascertained on Monday that the economic crisis in Russia was not
only the development of a conjunction of circumstances, but also
stems from deeper reason as well.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after talks with his visiting French counterpart,
Lionel Jospin, Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis said that they
ascertained that the reasons for this development were not only
conjunctural but also deeper, there were some structural reasons
which they should study in the long term.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) should deal in depth with the Russian
problem because there was great concern over the crisis, its
length and scope, he added.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Jospin, who arrived in Greece on Monday, said
that both sides ascertained that beyond the financial aspect of
the problem, there were also problems relating to a political
balance in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also discussed issues concerning the
Austrian-led October EU summit, and Simitis stressed that they had
reached agreement on the general course of the issues to be raised
there.  
</P>
</TEXT>
